    "tipid": "28",
    "section": "51104",
    "tip":
        "<div><ul><li>Do not use abbreviations. For example: Instead of writing &ldquo;BDE&rdquo; , write &ldquo;Business Development Executive&rdquo;<\/li><\/ul><\/div><ul><li>It is advisable to enter your job responsibilities in bullet format rather than in paragraph form<\/li><li>Give more emphasis to your more recent work experience<\/li><li>More than reading, employers scan resumes. You must be concrete and quantify your responsibilities<\/li><li>Be accurate and precise and detail the duties most relevant to the desired job<\/li><li>Focus your experience on the aspired position. Avoid including any unrelated experience or put it in a separate section<\/li><li>If your work experience is not relevant for the prospective job, but you have a volunteer experience or a community service highly related to it,&nbsp; you can add this experience detailing skills and abilities rather than companies or jobs<\/li><li>Include at least three bulleted items per job experience, showing first the most relevant duties<\/li><li>If you have had periods of unemployment think about the activities you were doing during that time: volunteer work, courses, classes, etc. List the activities or educational activities you did during that periods<\/li><\/ul>",
    "dateCreated": "2017-02-16 04:53:02",
    "status": "1"
  },
