  {
    "tipid": "32",
    "section": "51124",
    "tip":
        "<div><ul><li>Sometimes, you don&#39;t know exactly who you should be addressing your letter to. In such a case &quot;To The Hiring Manager&quot; is absolutely fine<\/li><li>Don&#39;t repeat your resume<\/li><li>Keep it short and simple<\/li><li>Write individual cover letters for every job you apply for. Even if the basics are the same you need to tailor it to each role to succeed<\/li><li>Remind the recruiter what they&#39;re looking for. Tell them you are what they&#39;re looking for (and explain how you fit the job description). Demonstrate why you are the best choice with examples&nbsp;<\/li><li>Showcase your skills<\/li><\/ul><\/div>",
